ural_normalized": false, "mention": "nitric oxide", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9984344244003296, "span": {"begin": 943, "end": 955}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:4842"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "nitric oxide synthase", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9670527577400208, "span": {"begin": 943, "end": 964}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Tip-DCs", "obj": "cell_line", "prob": 0.8071392774581909, "span": {"begin": 1000, "end": 1007}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "inflammatory dermal DCs", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.639850914478302, "span": {"begin": 1011, "end": 1034}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "moDCs", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.6955852508544922, "span": {"begin": 1055, "end": 1060}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:51284"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "TLR7", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9943771958351135, "span": {"begin": 1140, "end": 1144}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "pDCs", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.7741009593009949, "span": {"begin": 1148, "end": 1152}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:51311"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "TLR8", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9902172088623047, "span": {"begin": 1158, "end": 1162}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "moDCs", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.920130729675293, "span": {"begin": 1166, "end": 1171}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Tip-DCs", "obj": "cell_line", "prob": 0.9654788970947266, "span": {"begin": 1176, "end": 1183}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Tip-DCs", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.6788597106933594, "span": {"begin": 1207, "end": 1214}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:51561"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "IL-23", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9833520650863647, "span": {"begin": 1253, "end": 1258}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "matured", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.8875406980514526, "span": {"begin": 1264, "end": 1271}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Tip-DCs", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.7262567281723022, "span": {"begin": 1272, "end": 1279}}], "text": "The molecular structure and function of TLR7 and TLR8 are evident based on sufficient scientific findings as mentioned above. The known mechanisms for stimulation of TLR7/8 by each ligand are initiated by the formation of homodimer. TLR7-mediated signaling in pDC is mediated in a MyD88-dependent fashion, which initiates an IRF7, IRAK1, TRAF6, TRAF3, and IKK&alpha;-mediated response, secreting vast amounts of IFN type 1 (Kawai and Akira. 2011).  Similarly, upon engagement of ligands in endosomes, TLR8 initiate the MyD88-dependent pathway culminating in synthesis and release of proinflammatory mediators, such as TNF-&alpha; via NF-&kappa;B activation (Tanji et al. 2015).  DC activation is known to be enhanced by IFN-&alpha; in the presence of TNF-&alpha; (Luft et al. 1998).  R848 induces IL-23 production from activated human monocyte-derived DCs (moDCs) by enhanced transcriptional activity (Schwarz et al. 2013).  TNF and inducible nitric oxide synthase&ndash;expressing DCs also known as Tip-DCs or inflammatory dermal DCs differentiates from moDCs by inflammation (H&auml;nsel et al. 2011).  As mentioned above, stimulation of TLR7 in pDCs, and TLR8 in moDCs and Tip-DCs leads to activation of Tip-DCs, which leads to the overproduction of IL-23 from matured Tip-DCs.", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:22:40 +0000 2026"}